title.narrative: Output 3.5 Government and non-governmental partners adopt risk-informed approaches to emergency preparedness, planning and response to humanitarian needs for child protection and HIV

description.narrative: A total of 64,542 (34,449 boys, 30,093 girls) in humanitarian situations were provided with psychosocial support, including access to child friendly spaces with intersectoral programming interventions. 46,685 (25,088 boys; 21,597 girls) unaccompanied and separated children benefitted from a formal UNICEF-supported (best interest assessment (BIA)/ best interest determination (BID) process. The national child protection in emergencies risk management plan has been drafted and will be validated by stakeholders in early 2020. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
